\r\n\r\nowncloud version: 6b4\r\n\r\n### client configuration\r\nbrowser: chrome\r\n\r\noperating system: windows\r\n\r\n### logs\r\n#### web server error log\r\nnothing logged\r\n\r\n#### owncloud log (data/owncloud.log)\r\nno log yet as install not complete...\r\n"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/28712958","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/5919#issuecomment-28712958","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/5919","id":28712958,"user":{"login":"jamesjwarren","id":1857944,"avatar_url":"https://identicons.github.com/3186ae5cf75ce0c2f36264f8e4ff1784.png","gravatar_id":null,"url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren","html_url":"https://github.com/jamesjwarren","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-11-18t16:27:44z","updated_at":"2013-11-18t16:27:44z","body":"interestingly i've started getting similar errors in the owncloud log of my v5 install, so it seems a server issue.\r\n\r\n'sqlstate[hy000] [2013] lost connection to mysql server at 'reading initial communication packet', system error: 111'"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/28714604","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/5919#issuecomment-28714604","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/5919","id":28714604,"user":{"login":"karlitschek","id":867445,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/87ce2b4531ee1a0c32b50e0d8f049224?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f06e7098636caebfc9c30c9f52eb905df.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"87ce2b4531ee1a0c32b50e0d8f049224","url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek","html_url":"https://github.com/karlitschek","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-11-18t16:44:35z","updated_at":"2013-11-18t16:44:35z","body":"hmm. if the php/owncloud can't talk to mysql \"reading initial communication packet'\" then it's most likely also a server problem. can you check if mysqld is running? can you check if there is something in the mysql logfile? what is the connection limit of mysql? it should be as high as the maximum number of apache processes."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/28716336","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/5919#issuecomment-28716336","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/5919","id":28716336,"user":{"login":"jamesjwarren","id":1857944,"avatar_url":"https://identicons.github.com/3186ae5cf75ce0c2f36264f8e4ff1784.png","gravatar_id":null,"url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren","html_url":"https://github.com/jamesjwarren","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-11-18t17:01:46z","updated_at":"2013-11-18t17:01:46z","body":"mysqld is running and database access is working for other websites on the server. i hadn't set a max_connections for mysql so presumably it was working with a default value, i've now set this equal to the number of apache servers. however i don't think this was causing an issue as my problem is still present. the mysql log file doesn't seem to show up anything out of the ordinary:\r\n\r\n131118 16:51:41 [note] event scheduler: purging the queue. 0 events\r\n131118 16:51:41  innodb: starting shutdown...\r\n131118 16:51:46  innodb: shutdown completed; log sequence number 0 83485014\r\n131118 16:51:46 [note] /usr/libexec/mysqld: shutdown complete\r\n\r\n131118 16:51:46 mysqld_safe mysqld from pid file /var/run/mysqld/mysqld.pid ended\r\n131118 16:51:48 mysqld_safe starting mysqld daemon with databases from /var/lib/mysql\r\n131118 16:51:48  innodb: initializing buffer pool, size = 8.0m\r\n131118 16:51:48  innodb: completed initialization of buffer pool\r\n131118 16:51:49  innodb: started; log sequence number 0 83485014\r\n131118 16:51:49 [note] event scheduler: loaded 0 events\r\n131118 16:51:49 [note] /usr/libexec/mysqld: ready for connections.\r\n"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/28733443","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/5919#issuecomment-28733443","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/5919","id":28733443,"user":{"login":"jamesjwarren","id":1857944,"avatar_url":"https://identicons.github.com/3186ae5cf75ce0c2f36264f8e4ff1784.png","gravatar_id":null,"url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren","html_url":"https://github.com/jamesjwarren","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jamesjwarren/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-11-18t20:12:55z","updated_at":"2013-11-18t20:13:32z","body":"seem to have fixed it by deleting the database user and creating a new user with a different name. even though i had already tried changing the password of the previous user account.\r\n\r\nthe v5 install was fixed by removing the bind to 127.0.0.1 in mysql config. the v5 was recently transferred from another server so that caused that issue.\r\n\r\nthanks a lot for all the tips and pointers."}]